<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>addMessage() accepts the following for the $parts argument:</p>

<pre><code> * @param array An array of {@link &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/wsdl#_message"&gt;http://www.w3.org/TR/wsdl#_message&lt;/a&gt; parts}
 * The array is constructed like: 'name of part' =&gt; 'part xml schema data type'
</code></pre>

<p>However in document/literal it's common (if not required, I'm not sure) to use the "element" attribute for the parts, instead of "type", to reference a defined element instead of a type.</p>

